WEBVTT

00:02.066 --> 00:02.500
This program is rated G

00:04.233 --> 00:07.300
and is suitable for
general audiences.

00:13.066 --> 00:17.900
♪ If I could catch
a snowflake ♪

00:18.033 --> 00:22.734
♪ I'd save it just for you ♪

00:22.867 --> 00:27.200
♪ Wrap it up in pretty paper ♪

00:27.333 --> 00:32.166
♪ Let Mr. Mailman take it to ♪

00:32.300 --> 00:36.867
♪ Your doorstep in the morning ♪

00:37.000 --> 00:40.867
♪ So you could know
my love is true... ♪

00:42.633 --> 00:46.233
♪ ...'Cause, darling... ♪

00:46.367 --> 00:47.433
Elizabeth!

00:47.567 --> 00:48.533
There you are.

00:48.667 --> 00:50.900
I wanted to introduce
Tom Burress, our new COO.

00:51.033 --> 00:52.900
Oh, uh... hello.

00:53.033 --> 00:55.300
Your mother tells me
you're at USC.

00:55.433 --> 00:57.834
Uh, yes,
I graduate in the Spring.

00:57.967 --> 00:59.233
With honors.

00:59.367 --> 01:00.700
Will you be joining
your mother's team at Etonnante?

01:00.834 --> 01:04.200
Elizabeth is in the graduate
journalism program.

01:04.333 --> 01:07.233
She just published a story
about predatory loans

01:07.367 --> 01:08.166
that is making quite the waves.

01:08.300 --> 01:09.967
You've chosen a field

01:10.100 --> 01:11.900
with very little
financial security.

01:12.033 --> 01:13.033
Well, and the ability

01:13.166 --> 01:14.700
to effect real,
meaningful change,

01:14.834 --> 01:16.266
and give a voice
to the voiceless.

01:16.400 --> 01:17.433
Nothing would make me happier

01:17.567 --> 01:19.667
than having Elizabeth
by my side,

01:19.800 --> 01:22.166
but she has her own path.

01:22.300 --> 01:24.166
I am really grateful
that my mom is just so support--

01:24.300 --> 01:26.300
Excuse me, Ms. Athens?

01:26.433 --> 01:27.834
You have a message
at the front desk.

01:29.033 --> 01:30.467
It was nice meeting you.

01:30.600 --> 01:31.700
You too.

01:33.934 --> 01:35.667
Oh, here's the Clarks.

01:35.800 --> 01:38.834
Hello!
Lovely to see you.

01:46.233 --> 01:48.066
Hi, uh,
I'm Elizabeth Athens.

01:48.200 --> 01:49.367
Hi, Ms. Athens?

01:49.500 --> 01:50.533
What can I do for you today?

01:50.667 --> 01:53.100
Oh, sorry, I was told
I have a message.

01:54.367 --> 01:57.100
Unfortunately,
I don't have a message for you.

01:57.233 --> 01:58.667
I've come to rescue you.

02:02.066 --> 02:03.600
Josh.

02:03.734 --> 02:05.266
From a Christmas party?

02:05.400 --> 02:06.900
That is not a Christmas party.

02:07.033 --> 02:09.633
That is a bunch of old men
in suits

02:09.767 --> 02:12.133
discussing
their investment portfolios.

02:12.266 --> 02:13.367
- That's not true.
- No?

02:13.500 --> 02:14.867
They're also
comparing their golf games.

02:15.000 --> 02:18.700
Come on, if we leave now,
we can make the Swapping Santa.

02:21.100 --> 02:23.333
My mother has been
asking about you.

02:23.467 --> 02:25.166
She made gingerbread cookies.

02:25.300 --> 02:27.333
The ones with
the little frosting bowties?

02:27.467 --> 02:28.400
You'd have to come
to find out.

02:28.533 --> 02:29.734
Don't worry,

02:29.867 --> 02:30.867
I'll get you back

02:31.000 --> 02:32.033
before you turn into a pumpkin.

02:32.166 --> 02:33.734
Let's go, come on, come on.

02:40.934 --> 02:43.333
♪ [singing] Deck the halls
with boughs of holly ♪

02:43.467 --> 02:46.166
♪ Fa-la-la-la-la
la-la-la-la ♪

02:46.300 --> 02:49.166
♪ 'Tis the season
to be jolly ♪

02:49.300 --> 02:50.533
♪ Fa-la-la-la-la
la-la-la-la ♪

02:50.667 --> 02:52.900
Oh, I feel
slightly over-dressed.

02:53.033 --> 02:54.000
Let's see?

02:54.133 --> 02:56.467
♪ Troll the ancient
yuletide carol... ♪

02:56.600 --> 02:57.633
- ♪ Fa-la-la-la-la... ♪
- Beautiful.

02:57.767 --> 03:00.800
♪ ...La-la-la-la ♪

03:00.934 --> 03:02.200
Elizabeth!

03:02.333 --> 03:04.266
I am so glad you made it!

03:04.400 --> 03:05.266
I promised her cookies, Ma.

03:05.400 --> 03:06.700
They're in the dining room,

03:06.834 --> 03:10.367
and I put a few extra
aside for you, so...

03:10.500 --> 03:13.166
Oh, thank you.

03:13.300 --> 03:15.033
- Josh told us the good news.
- Oh...

03:15.166 --> 03:17.900
We are just
so proud of you two.

03:18.033 --> 03:19.066
Betty!

03:19.200 --> 03:21.467
Is that your famous
figgy pudding I see?

03:23.233 --> 03:25.734
Hold it,
I got a surprise for you.

03:25.867 --> 03:26.867
I think it's in the kitchen.

03:27.000 --> 03:28.934
In addition to the cookies?

03:29.066 --> 03:30.533
Yes, you're gonna get
so many cookies.

03:30.667 --> 03:31.500
Just hold on.

03:31.633 --> 03:32.800
Okay.

03:35.066 --> 03:36.266
Andy?

03:37.967 --> 03:39.133
You're home? Come here!

03:39.266 --> 03:41.734
Oh, my gosh!

03:41.867 --> 03:43.233
I thought you were in Atlanta
for the holidays.

03:43.367 --> 03:44.800
Change of plans.

03:44.934 --> 03:46.033
You did not tell me.

03:46.166 --> 03:47.967
That wouldn't make it
a very good surprise, would it?

03:48.100 --> 03:50.734
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

03:50.867 --> 03:51.900
Cheers.

03:52.033 --> 03:53.500
- What?
- Yes.

03:53.633 --> 03:54.200
Aw...

03:54.333 --> 03:55.767
Wait for it.
Oh?

03:57.600 --> 03:59.233
Well, that's the best surprise.

04:00.333 --> 04:01.734
I'm so glad you're home.

04:01.867 --> 04:03.400
Come here.

04:06.433 --> 04:07.367
All right, come here.

04:07.500 --> 04:08.533
- Come on,
- Group hug, group hug.

04:08.667 --> 04:09.934
There's room
for all three of us here.

04:11.767 --> 04:13.300
...So Lizzie's camped out
in front of the Dean's office

04:13.433 --> 04:14.467
for hours--

04:14.600 --> 04:15.934
Well, it's the worst story.

04:16.066 --> 04:17.066
- No, it's not.
- Yes, it is.

04:17.200 --> 04:19.233
trying desperately
to wait him out

04:19.367 --> 04:20.900
to get a quote for our story.

04:21.033 --> 04:22.934
Okay, in a battle of wills,
I'm taking Lizzie every time.

04:23.066 --> 04:24.200
Yes, except for this time,

04:24.333 --> 04:25.767
because the Dean
had already gone home,

04:25.900 --> 04:27.900
and she was in a standoff
with an empty chair.

04:29.100 --> 04:30.734
Not the whole truth.

04:30.867 --> 04:32.800
No, no, no, no,
someone had tipped him off!

04:32.934 --> 04:34.200
So, did you get your quote?

04:34.333 --> 04:35.800
No. He's still dodging us.

04:35.934 --> 04:36.834
Well, who wouldn't,

04:36.967 --> 04:38.100
with Woodward and Bernstein
on your tail?

04:39.266 --> 04:40.834
Wait, did you tell him?

04:40.967 --> 04:42.300
Tell me what?

04:42.433 --> 04:45.033
We got an offer
to work for the New York Times.

04:45.166 --> 04:45.934
- What?
- Yeah.

04:46.066 --> 04:47.033
Amazing.

04:47.166 --> 04:49.000
Yeah, we start
after graduation.

04:49.133 --> 04:50.433
Yeah, I can't believe it.

04:50.567 --> 04:52.600
It's everything I--
well, we have ever wanted.

04:52.734 --> 04:56.000
We have an actual chance
to make a difference now.

04:56.133 --> 04:57.033
Oh, hey, there's a good one.

04:58.133 --> 04:59.633
- Yes.
- Oh...

04:59.767 --> 05:01.667
we are a little old
for Christmas wishes.

05:01.800 --> 05:03.133
It's tradition.

05:03.266 --> 05:04.333
It's tradition.
Come on, let's go,

05:04.467 --> 05:05.967
- everybody up.
- Yup.

05:06.100 --> 05:07.033
Close your eyes.

05:17.000 --> 05:17.934
What did you wish for?

05:18.066 --> 05:19.800
This.

05:19.934 --> 05:22.433
Another Christmas
with my two best friends.

05:23.333 --> 05:24.367
Selfie time!

05:24.500 --> 05:26.767
- Selfie time.
- Merry Christmas, guys.

05:26.900 --> 05:28.200
- Cheers.
- Cheers!

05:52.767 --> 05:53.400
I know, sorry.

05:53.533 --> 05:54.567
It's just holiday traffic.

05:54.700 --> 05:57.633
Yup, no,
I'm heading in right now.

06:06.734 --> 06:07.800
Hi.

06:20.367 --> 06:21.900
Sweetheart...

06:22.033 --> 06:24.333
I have a very important
question for you.

06:24.467 --> 06:26.367
- For the Christmas gala.
- Oh, um...

06:26.500 --> 06:27.934
I like the black.

06:28.066 --> 06:29.066
Really?

06:29.200 --> 06:30.934
Or the green.

06:31.066 --> 06:32.100
That's what I thought, too.

06:32.233 --> 06:33.333
Monica called

06:33.467 --> 06:34.800
and asked if we should
include a plus one

06:34.934 --> 06:35.967
on your invitation.

06:36.100 --> 06:37.367
Uh, no, not this year.

06:37.500 --> 06:40.533
You know, I think
Rosalie's son's in town.

06:40.667 --> 06:42.834
You two really hit it off
at the Spring mixer.

06:44.834 --> 06:45.867
Elizabeth,

06:46.000 --> 06:47.133
when is the last time
you had a date?

06:47.266 --> 06:49.567
Uh... I date.

06:50.433 --> 06:52.767
Honey, you don't date.

06:52.900 --> 06:55.400
You have networking lunches
and business meetings.

06:55.533 --> 06:57.333
I should really get this.

06:57.467 --> 06:58.867
You know,
it'd be good for you.

06:59.000 --> 07:00.533
Meet new people,
put yourself out there.

07:00.667 --> 07:01.867
You don't need
to worry about me.

07:02.000 --> 07:04.433
Honey, there's
a whole world outside.

07:04.567 --> 07:06.333
Things that
you're gonna miss out on

07:06.467 --> 07:07.934
hiding in here.

07:08.066 --> 07:10.033
It's 10:00 a.m. on a Monday,
I'm not hiding.

07:11.233 --> 07:13.767
I should really get this.

07:13.900 --> 07:15.033
Honey...

07:22.734 --> 07:23.800
Hey, Madelyn.

07:23.934 --> 07:25.467
It's me.

07:25.600 --> 07:27.200
It's been a minute, huh?

07:27.333 --> 07:28.400
I got your new number,

07:28.533 --> 07:29.967
and I wanted to call you,

07:30.100 --> 07:31.000
I hope that's okay.

07:31.133 --> 07:33.467
I'm sure you're surprised
to hear from me,

07:33.600 --> 07:35.066
but I've been
thinking about you...

07:35.200 --> 07:36.066
about us

07:36.200 --> 07:37.500
a lot.

07:37.633 --> 07:39.300
I got in this morning,

07:39.433 --> 07:41.533
and I even stopped
at Sweeteats.

07:41.667 --> 07:43.233
They still have
those caramel turtles

07:43.367 --> 07:44.967
you like so much.

07:45.100 --> 07:46.300
I miss you, Maddy.

07:46.433 --> 07:48.800
I know I've made
a lot of mistakes,

07:48.934 --> 07:51.166
but I'm trying
to make things right.

07:51.300 --> 07:53.133
I know you're probably busy
with the holidays,

07:53.266 --> 07:57.800
but if there is any chance
that you feel the same,

07:57.934 --> 08:00.400
I'll be at our spot,
Christmas Eve, 9:00.

08:00.533 --> 08:01.400
I hope to see you there,

08:01.533 --> 08:02.633
but if I don't,

08:02.767 --> 08:03.900
I understand.

08:12.600 --> 08:14.400
Hello, Guildcrest Hotel.

08:14.533 --> 08:16.233
Hi, um... I received
a call at this number.

08:16.367 --> 08:17.333
Name?

08:17.467 --> 08:19.533
Uh, my name
is Elizabeth Athens.

08:19.667 --> 08:21.367
No, the name of the person
you're trying to reach.

08:21.500 --> 08:23.600
Oh, I don't know.

08:23.734 --> 08:26.433
He didn't leave his name, actually.

08:26.567 --> 08:27.800
I just, I was hoping
you could tell me.

08:27.934 --> 08:29.000
It could be any of the guests

08:29.133 --> 08:30.934
making an outgoing call
from their room.

08:31.066 --> 08:32.133
They all route
through the front desk.

08:32.266 --> 08:33.133
Oh.

08:34.500 --> 08:35.433
Well, thank you.

08:35.567 --> 08:37.100
Have a very merry Christmas.

08:37.233 --> 08:38.166
You, too.

09:00.166 --> 09:01.934
Housekeeping!

09:02.066 --> 09:03.300
Just a moment.

09:34.600 --> 09:35.867
He probably
realized his mistake

09:36.000 --> 09:37.166
the moment he hung up the phone.

09:37.300 --> 09:39.400
But what if he didn't?

09:39.533 --> 09:40.867
Oh, well, I wouldn't
worry about it.

09:41.000 --> 09:42.800
A couple days of no response,

09:42.934 --> 09:44.767
and, you know,
he'll put it together.

09:44.900 --> 09:46.667
It just doesn't feel right
to erase the message.

09:46.800 --> 09:48.200
He poured his heart out.

09:48.333 --> 09:49.967
To someone else.

09:50.100 --> 09:52.300
You were never meant
to hear that message.

09:52.433 --> 09:54.533
I just keep picturing him
sitting there on Christmas Eve,

09:54.667 --> 09:56.667
and he's waiting for her
to walk through the door,

09:56.800 --> 09:59.100
and he's thinking
she just stood him up.

09:59.233 --> 10:01.900
Well, there's nothing
you can do about it now.

10:02.033 --> 10:05.033
You don't know
anything about him.

10:15.266 --> 10:16.667
He is one of your guests.

10:16.800 --> 10:18.333
We have 1,500 rooms.

10:18.467 --> 10:19.400
Fully booked for the holidays.

10:19.533 --> 10:20.934
That's over 3,000 guests.

10:21.066 --> 10:21.967
There's got be some way
to find out

10:22.100 --> 10:23.333
which one of them
made the phone call.

10:23.467 --> 10:24.600
As I explained before,

10:24.734 --> 10:26.166
- if you don't have a name--
- I understand.

10:26.300 --> 10:27.333
I would not be here

10:27.467 --> 10:28.533
if this was not very,
very important

10:28.667 --> 10:29.967
that I get this message to him.

10:30.100 --> 10:32.700
Look, I even wrote it down,
word for word.

10:32.834 --> 10:35.100
That's everything
on my voicemail.

10:35.233 --> 10:36.133
Ma'am, I can't...

10:36.266 --> 10:37.767
But can you just put it
in the hotel lobby,

10:37.900 --> 10:38.867
or go door to door.

10:39.000 --> 10:40.800
Please do something,
it's Christmas.

10:40.934 --> 10:43.033
I am asking you just to try.

10:43.166 --> 10:46.066
Have you never had a regret
that was just so big,

10:46.200 --> 10:47.600
that you would do anything
for a second chance

10:47.734 --> 10:49.133
to make it right?

10:50.800 --> 10:52.367
I wish I could help, I do...

10:53.767 --> 10:55.166
...but my hands are tied.

10:56.367 --> 10:58.200
Welcome
to the Guildcrest Hotel.

10:58.333 --> 11:00.200
Checking in?

11:04.834 --> 11:06.200
You're back.

11:06.333 --> 11:08.000
Sir?

11:08.133 --> 11:08.967
Hart.

11:09.100 --> 11:10.266
Josh Hart.

11:11.467 --> 11:12.633
Please review here and sign,

11:12.767 --> 11:14.133
and we'll get you checked in.

11:15.400 --> 11:16.367
Excuse me

11:16.500 --> 11:18.533
Yeah, right...

11:18.667 --> 11:20.066
I'll go this way.

11:25.934 --> 11:28.233
Here, just, um, please...

11:28.367 --> 11:30.066
do the right thing.

11:36.066 --> 11:37.333
All right, here's your key.

11:37.467 --> 11:38.467
Room 314.

11:38.600 --> 11:40.266
Just right to the right.

11:40.400 --> 11:41.900
Thanks.

11:42.033 --> 11:44.033
Welcome to
the Guildcrest hotel.

11:44.166 --> 11:45.400
Checking in?

11:54.767 --> 11:56.133
Elizabeth!

11:56.266 --> 11:59.166
The clerk tossed it
as soon as you left.

11:59.300 --> 12:00.433
Oh.

12:00.567 --> 12:02.467
So much for
Goodwill Towards Men.

12:02.600 --> 12:04.500
Who's Madelyn?

12:04.633 --> 12:06.767
I don't know.

12:06.900 --> 12:07.900
It was a wrong number,

12:08.033 --> 12:09.567
and I was just
delivering the message.

12:09.700 --> 12:10.934
It's in their hands now.

12:11.066 --> 12:14.200
Actually, it's in mine.

12:14.333 --> 12:15.500
It...

12:15.633 --> 12:17.066
Christmas Eve
is in three days.

12:17.200 --> 12:18.667
I know.

12:18.800 --> 12:20.000
So, what are you going to do?

12:20.133 --> 12:21.600
Nothing.

12:21.734 --> 12:23.033
It's not my problem.

12:23.166 --> 12:23.834
I did my part.

12:23.967 --> 12:26.266
The hotel isn't going to help.

12:26.400 --> 12:27.400
What am I supposed to do?

12:27.533 --> 12:28.600
There's thousands of guests.

12:28.734 --> 12:29.700
I don't have a single lead.

12:29.834 --> 12:31.667
That's never stopped you before.

12:31.800 --> 12:36.033
Yeah, well, things change.

12:36.166 --> 12:37.667
People change.

12:37.800 --> 12:40.133
You'd know that
if you stuck around.

12:53.066 --> 12:53.767
Hi, Ma.

12:53.900 --> 12:55.633
There's my boy.

12:56.867 --> 12:58.500
All right, all right.

13:00.734 --> 13:01.533
Where are your bags?

13:01.667 --> 13:02.533
I got a room

13:02.667 --> 13:03.967
- at the Guildcrest.
- What?

13:04.100 --> 13:04.934
You got a full house here,

13:05.066 --> 13:05.967
Charlotte, Keith, the baby...

13:06.100 --> 13:07.767
Nonsense, we can make space.

13:07.900 --> 13:09.700
I had your father
bring down the rollout.

13:09.834 --> 13:10.700
Well, as luxurious
as that sounds,

13:10.834 --> 13:12.300
I think
for the sake of my back,

13:12.433 --> 13:13.600
- I'm gonna stick to the hotel.
- No, I--

13:13.734 --> 13:14.867
It's all right,
come on, what do you need?

13:15.000 --> 13:16.834
You got a lot of bags here.

13:16.967 --> 13:19.667
Yeah. I stopped at
Halliday's Christmas market,

13:19.800 --> 13:20.834
I picked up a few things.

13:20.967 --> 13:22.700
Wow, thank you.
You got it?

13:22.834 --> 13:23.600
- Got it.
- Okay, good.

13:23.734 --> 13:24.867
No peeking.

13:25.000 --> 13:27.834
Yeah, no, I can't see
anything here, Ma.

13:34.633 --> 13:36.667
It might be nice to reconnect
with some old friends

13:36.800 --> 13:39.467
while you're back...

13:43.266 --> 13:45.433
Does she know
you're here for Christmas?

13:45.567 --> 13:47.000
Trying to get rid of me
already?

13:48.233 --> 13:51.867
I am so happy
to have you home.

13:54.000 --> 13:56.233
It's been too long.

13:56.367 --> 13:58.100
I know.

14:04.934 --> 14:07.900
...If there is any chance

14:08.033 --> 14:09.734
that you feel the same,

14:09.867 --> 14:13.400
I'll be at our spot
Christmas Eve. 9:00.

14:13.533 --> 14:14.567
I hope to see you there,

14:14.700 --> 14:16.200
but if I don't,

14:16.333 --> 14:17.567
I understand.

14:25.900 --> 14:27.367
I'm in the city for a few days.

14:27.500 --> 14:31.600
I got in this morning,
and I thought of you.

14:31.734 --> 14:35.300
I even stopped at Sweeteats.

15:05.967 --> 15:07.734
♪ Peace, peace, peace ♪

15:07.867 --> 15:10.934
♪ And joy, joy, joy ♪

15:11.066 --> 15:14.000
♪ And love, love, love ♪

15:14.133 --> 15:18.600
♪ Let's fill the world with ♪

15:18.734 --> 15:20.400
♪ Peace, peace, peace ♪

15:20.533 --> 15:23.467
♪ And joy, joy, joy ♪

15:23.600 --> 15:26.700
♪ And love, love, love ♪

15:26.834 --> 15:30.533
♪ Let's fill the world with ♪

15:30.667 --> 15:33.333
♪ Love ♪

15:35.066 --> 15:35.967
Wait, so what are your plans

15:36.100 --> 15:37.166
after graduation?

15:37.300 --> 15:38.934
Are you still
thinking about traveling?

15:39.066 --> 15:42.333
Actually, I think
I might come home, for good.

15:42.467 --> 15:43.867
Really?

15:44.000 --> 15:46.400
I've got
my whole life to travel

15:46.533 --> 15:47.500
I miss this place.

15:47.633 --> 15:48.667
The people...

15:48.800 --> 15:50.433
you.

15:51.900 --> 15:53.233
I'm really glad
you came tonight.

15:53.367 --> 15:55.934
I was hoping, um...

15:56.066 --> 15:57.800
I could talk to you
about something

15:57.934 --> 15:58.967
A good something, or...

15:59.100 --> 16:00.734
Good.
Well, hopefully.

16:00.867 --> 16:02.133
It's just about the future,

16:02.266 --> 16:03.533
about the things I want
in my life.

16:03.667 --> 16:05.600
About us.

16:05.734 --> 16:06.734
Us?

16:06.867 --> 16:07.667
All right, everyone!

16:07.800 --> 16:09.800
It's time for Swapping Santa!

16:09.934 --> 16:11.867
Grab your gifts
and join the circle!

16:12.000 --> 16:13.166
♪ Peace, peace, peace ♪

16:13.300 --> 16:14.867
- ♪ And joy, joy, joy ♪
- Later.

16:15.000 --> 16:16.533
♪ And joy, joy, joy ♪

16:16.667 --> 16:19.166
♪ And love, love, love ♪

16:19.300 --> 16:23.633
♪ Let's fill the world with ♪

16:23.767 --> 16:25.767
♪ Peace, peace, peace ♪

16:25.900 --> 16:28.934
